1 Configuration

Configuration of project directory & analysis outputs:

Show full config

source(here("rr_helpers.R"))

# Set up outputs
message("Document index: ", doc_id)
## Document index: 02
# Specify where to save outputs
out        <- here("output", doc_id); dir.create(out, recursive = TRUE)
figout     <- here("figures", doc_id, "/")
cache      <- paste0("~/tmp/", basename(here()), "/", doc_id, "/")

5 Analysis

We can use the rr_ggplot wrapper to save source data alongside the resulting ggplot, as long as we specify the number of the plot in the chunk.

mtcars2 %>% 
    rr_ggplot(1, aes(x = disp, y = wt)) +
    geom_line() +
    theme_bw()
## ...writing source data of ggplot to rr/figures/02//figure2-1.source_data.tsv

mtcars2 %>% 
    rr_ggplot(2, aes(x = disp, y = wt)) +
    geom_point() +
    theme_bw()
## ...writing source data of ggplot to rr/figures/02//figure2-2.source_data.tsv
